<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="164" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1537,1742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName box="[199,332,1574,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis box="[199,332,1574,1597]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">M. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Darjeeling, north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1042,1573,1598]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arita" box="[1059,1342,1573,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="164" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1996) A Revision of Ferdinand Le Cerf's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae), Kept at the Paris Museum. I. The Genus Melittia Hubner, [1819] in the Oriental and Australian Regions. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 2 (2), 137 - 187." type="journal article" year="1996">Arita &amp; Gorbunov 1996</bibRefCitation>
). It also occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[258,353,1609,1634]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arita" box="[367,639,1609,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="164" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (2000) On the tribe Melittiini (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) of Vietnam. Tinea, 16 (4), 252 - 291." type="journal article" year="2000">Arita &amp; Gorbunov 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and is here recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1011,1609,1634]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time. It can be recognized by its wide discal spot of the forewing with its short projection into the anterior transparent area, the broad apical area, the blue-metallic hue of the anal area of the hindwing and bright yellow hairs on the hind leg dorsally and the patches of white and blue hairs ventrally, which give the hind leg a chequered appearance.
</paragraph>
